# Status Updates

- One JSON object per line in [status.jsonl](mdc:internal/StatusUpdate/status.jsonl). Keep entries concise; long notes belong in `Status_Extended.md`.
- Validate shape against [status.schema.json](mdc:internal/StatusUpdate/status.schema.json). Required: `ts`, `component`, `status`, `summary`, `changes`, `next`, `blockers`, `classification`, `version`.
- Use the minimal template in [STATUS_UPDATE_TEMPLATE.md](mdc:internal/StatusUpdate/STATUS_UPDATE_TEMPLATE.md).

Example line

```json
{"ts":"2025-08-08T00:00:00Z","component":"<Area>","status":"planned","summary":"<1–3 sentence summary>","changes":["<change1>"],"next":["<next1>"],"blockers":[],"metrics":{},"refs":[{"type":"file","path":"internal/qualia/TODO.md","note":"tracking"}],"classification":"Confidential — Internal Use Only","version":1}
```

- Status values: `planned`, `in_progress`, `done`, `blocked`.
- Classification must be exactly: `Confidential — Internal Use Only`.

